    thinking: "**Defining the Architecture**\n\nOkay, I\'m aiming for a React single-page app to visualize 3D building shadows on a city map. The technologies will be React, Vite, Tailwind CSS, and TypeScript. For the map, I\'m thinking MapLibre GL JS combined with Deck.gl. I\'ll need Deck.gl\'s `SunLight` or effects for the shadow rendering and perform solar calculations.\n\n\n**Refining Dependency Selections**\n\nI\'ve revised the dependency list for the project. I\'m focusing on `maplibre-gl`, `react-map-gl`, and the necessary Deck.gl packages (`@deck.gl/react`, `@deck.gl/core`, `@deck.gl/layers`, `@deck.gl/geo-layers`, and `@deck.gl/mapbox`). I had initially overlooked the best integration for Deck.gl with React, opting for react-map-gl to work well with maplibre-gl.\n\n\n"
