    thinking: "**Considering Performance Implications**\n\nI\'m now focusing on performance. Overpass\'s rate limits and potential slowness are a concern. I\'ve been researching native extrusion with `fill-extrusion` in MapLibre GL, and its interplay with standard Mapbox styles. There\'s a tricky issue of shadows, but I\'m looking into how to enable them to make things work.\n\n\n**Exploring Shadow Casting with Deck.gl**\n\nI\'ve shifted focus to Deck.gl for native shadow casting. I realized that MapLibre GL lacks true 3D shadows, unlike Mapbox. I\'ll need to use OSM vector tiles for building data since it is free, and found `https://data.osmbuildings.org/` offers GeoJSON tiles. Protomaps initially seemed good, but the managed service requires an API key, so that\'s out. I am considering debouncing Overpass API requests with an initial view from static GeoJSON.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 11
      nanos: 828821277
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
