ing Component Placement**\n\nI\'m now restructuring the layout within `ControlPanel.tsx`. My current focus is shifting the metrics and \"Snap to GH\" button to a right-side panel, while keeping the timeline slider at the bottom. The HTML provides a template for an absolute-positioned right panel. By splitting the existing grid into two absolute containers within the same component, I\'m aiming for a perfect visual alignment with the immersive UI design. This includes the current time, timezone offset, slider, and the golden/blue hour indicators. This new structure seems promising!\n\n\n**Implementing Component Placement**\n\nI\'m now implementing the component placement based on the immersive UI layout. I\'m focusing on the `ControlPanel.tsx`, separating it into right and bottom panels. I\'m moving solar metrics and time information to the right, and the timeline slider to the bottom. I\'m also styling the \"Snap to Golden Hour\" button. In `SearchOverlay.tsx`, I am styling the overlay and inputs in alignment with the immersive UI design using styles such as rounded-full, border-white/10, bg-white/5, and more.\n\n\n"
